1783 typedef asn1::enumerated<msg_opts> msg_types;
1784 struct nas_5gs_hdr {
1785  enum security_header_type_opts {
1786  plain_5gs_nas_message,
1787  integrity_protected,
1788  integrity_protected_and_ciphered,
1789  integrity_protected_with_new_5G_nas_context,
1790  integrity_protected_and_ciphered_with_new_5G_nas_context
1791  };
1792 
1793  enum extended_protocol_discriminator_opts {
1794  extended_protocol_discriminator_5gsm = 0x2e,
1795  extended_protocol_discriminator_5gmm = 0x7e,
1796  };
1797 
1798  // Outer
1799  extended_protocol_discriminator_opts extended_protocol_discriminator = extended_protocol_discriminator_5gsm;
1800  security_header_type_opts security_header_type = plain_5gs_nas_message;
1801  // Only valid if not plain
1802  uint8_t sequence_number = 0xff;
1803  uint32_t message_authentication_code = 0x00000000;
1804  // Only valid if 5gsm type
1805  uint8_t pdu_session_identity = 0xff;
1806  uint8_t procedure_transaction_identity = 0xff;
1807  // Inner
1808  extended_protocol_discriminator_opts inner_extended_protocol_discriminator = extended_protocol_discriminator_5gsm;
1809  security_header_type_opts inner_security_header_type = plain_5gs_nas_message;
1810 
1811  msg_types message_type = msg_types::options::nulltype;
1812 
1813  SRSASN_CODE pack(asn1::bit_ref& bref);
1814  SRSASN_CODE pack_outer(asn1::bit_ref& bref);
1815  SRSASN_CODE unpack(asn1::cbit_ref& bref);
1816  SRSASN_CODE unpack_outer(asn1::cbit_ref& bref);
1817 };
